1
00:00:19,433 --> 00:00:22,433
One emergency call,
my life turns upside down.

2
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:25,167
Will they expect me to go
all the way to Sorsogon?

3
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:26,667
Who I will go home to there?

4
00:00:26,733 --> 00:00:29,267
My father? The man
who broke my mother's heart?

5
00:00:29,333 --> 00:00:31,500
I already fixed
your two-day itinerary.

6
00:00:31,567 --> 00:00:33,867
As soon as you arrive
at Legazpi Domestic Airport,

7
00:00:33,967 --> 00:00:36,667
the driver will pick you up
from car rental services.

8
00:00:36,733 --> 00:00:39,400
You thought that Mr. Estrellado
is already gone?

9
00:00:39,467 --> 00:00:40,500
That's not it.

10
00:00:40,567 --> 00:00:42,867
He's gone as in he went home
already.

11
00:00:42,933 --> 00:00:44,467
I'm getting older.

12
00:00:44,533 --> 00:00:48,000
You should let me be a part
of your life.

13
00:00:48,067 --> 00:00:49,633
Maybe not, Father.

14
00:00:49,700 --> 00:00:51,867
I'm okay.
I'm used to being alone.

15
00:00:51,933 --> 00:00:54,367
Now, if you want to be a part
of my life,

16
00:00:54,433 --> 00:00:55,733
you should've done that
a long time ago.

17
00:00:55,800 --> 00:00:57,467
When my mother was still alive
and when I was still young.

18
00:00:59,933 --> 00:01:00,633
How are you, Mother?

19
00:01:41,767 --> 00:01:45,500
I'm sorry if I just visited you
now.

20
00:01:50,367 --> 00:01:52,533
You know that when I come home
here in Sorsogon,

21
00:01:56,933 --> 00:01:59,167
all I remember...

22
00:02:02,433 --> 00:02:04,267
are the bad things
that happened to our family.

23
00:02:06,900 --> 00:02:08,833
Do you think father
will like this?

24
00:02:10,567 --> 00:02:12,533
Of course, he will like that.

25
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:16,633
Look, this is perfect.

26
00:02:16,733 --> 00:02:18,933
You're a better dressmaker
than me, my Child.

27
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,867
- Not really.
- It's beautiful.

28
00:02:20,933 --> 00:02:22,467
- Really?
- It will suit him.

29
00:02:25,467 --> 00:02:26,267
Father is here.

30
00:02:36,433 --> 00:02:37,467
Happy Birthday, Father!

31
00:02:40,333 --> 00:02:42,633
- Oh right, it's my birthday...
- I have a gift for you.

32
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:46,600
I hope you like what I made,
Father.

33
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:47,333
My Child, thank you.

34
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:50,233
Happy birthday, Love.

35
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:54,800
Lucinda, we need to talk.

36
00:02:56,433 --> 00:02:58,167
I have something important
to tell you.

37
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:05,000
Celeste, my Child, can you leave
me and your mother for a while?

38
00:03:05,067 --> 00:03:05,500
Okay.

39
00:03:30,867 --> 00:03:33,433
Love, I'm worried.

40
00:03:34,933 --> 00:03:35,767
What's the problem?

41
00:03:38,233 --> 00:03:38,900
Lucinda,

42
00:03:40,667 --> 00:03:41,267
I...

43
00:03:45,633 --> 00:03:46,833
I love someone else.

44
00:03:54,267 --> 00:03:54,900
Patricio.

45
00:03:58,167 --> 00:03:58,600
How...

46
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:03,933
can you do this to me?

47
00:04:07,667 --> 00:04:09,267
I gave you everything, right?

48
00:04:13,267 --> 00:04:15,000
What does she have that I don't?

49
00:04:17,967 --> 00:04:18,900
Is she more beautiful?

50
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:23,133
Is she a better cook?

51
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:26,533
Is she more caring to you?

52
00:04:31,467 --> 00:04:34,233
Patricio, whatever my mistakes
are, whatever my shortcomings,

53
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:35,233
I will correct it.

54
00:04:36,567 --> 00:04:38,233
Just leave that woman!

55
00:04:39,167 --> 00:04:40,500
Lucinda, I can't...

56
00:04:43,967 --> 00:04:46,800
I can't leave Adora anymore.

57
00:04:49,333 --> 00:04:50,000
She is pregnant.

58
00:04:53,433 --> 00:04:53,767
Love.

59
00:04:56,400 --> 00:05:00,967
Love, how about our daughter?

60
00:05:01,067 --> 00:05:03,300
How about Celeste?

61
00:05:03,367 --> 00:05:05,833
Love, you love me, right?

62
00:05:05,900 --> 00:05:08,433
You love me, right, Patricio?

63
00:05:14,133 --> 00:05:16,567
Celeste... how about Celeste?

64
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:25,667
No.

65
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:29,400
Love...

66
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:36,567
how about our daughter?

67
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:42,000
Love, my Love.

68
00:05:42,067 --> 00:05:43,000
Love.

69
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:02,267
Don't do this to us.

70
00:06:02,333 --> 00:06:04,300
Don't do this to us, Love.

71
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:06,733
Love...

72
00:06:41,733 --> 00:06:44,600
Help me, Lord.

73
00:06:48,267 --> 00:06:51,000
Help me to bring my family back.

74
00:06:53,267 --> 00:06:55,200
Bring back Patricio to us.

75
00:06:57,667 --> 00:07:01,933
Our Father, help me.

76
00:07:25,300 --> 00:07:25,733
Mother.

77
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:28,000
Come on, let's eat.

78
00:07:33,867 --> 00:07:38,067
Mother, you haven't eaten
since this morning.

79
00:07:39,533 --> 00:07:40,633
Let's eat.

80
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:46,567
Mother, you will get sick.

81
00:07:48,167 --> 00:07:49,367
Come on, Mother.

82
00:08:13,067 --> 00:08:14,267
Don't cry.

83
00:08:57,400 --> 00:09:01,067
Mother, don't wait for father
anymore.

84
00:09:04,100 --> 00:09:05,633
He won't come back to us.

85
00:09:09,267 --> 00:09:10,500
Your father will come back.

86
00:09:15,267 --> 00:09:16,667
He loves me so much.

87
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:21,267
He loves the two of us so much.

88
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:46,667
Mother, don't cry.

89
00:10:17,400 --> 00:10:20,633
Mother, let's go to sleep.

90
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,100
It's already midnight.

91
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:29,067
Mother, come on.

92
00:10:31,300 --> 00:10:33,333
You've been crying
and losing sleep for weeks now.

93
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:34,200
Come on, Mother,
you should sleep.

94
00:10:35,933 --> 00:10:37,000
Mother, go to sleep.

95
00:11:14,300 --> 00:11:15,500
Mother, let's eat.

96
00:11:18,700 --> 00:11:18,900
Mother.

97
00:11:21,833 --> 00:11:22,067
Mother?

98
00:11:23,433 --> 00:11:23,700
Mother?

99
00:11:24,767 --> 00:11:25,267
Mother, wake up.

100
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:28,367
Mother... Mother, let's eat.

101
00:11:29,167 --> 00:11:29,400
Mother?

102
00:11:30,467 --> 00:11:31,600
No, no, no.

103
00:11:31,667 --> 00:11:32,800
Mother, this isn't it, right?

104
00:11:33,833 --> 00:11:34,133
Mother!

105
00:11:35,100 --> 00:11:35,600
Mother...

106
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:38,700
Mother, wake up!

107
00:11:38,767 --> 00:11:39,933
No.

108
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,267
This is not true, right?

109
00:11:41,367 --> 00:11:42,900
Mother, no.

110
00:11:42,967 --> 00:11:43,967
Mother, wake up.

111
00:11:44,033 --> 00:11:45,333
Wake up, Mother.

112
00:11:45,400 --> 00:11:47,033
Mother, no.

113
00:11:47,100 --> 00:11:52,167
Mother, this isn't true, right?

114
00:11:52,233 --> 00:11:53,700
Mother, no.

115
00:11:54,967 --> 00:11:55,633
Mother, no.

116
00:11:56,467 --> 00:11:57,600
No, no.

117
00:11:57,667 --> 00:11:57,933
Mother.

118
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:01,433
Wake up, Mother.

119
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:02,800
Mother, wake up! Wake up!

120
00:12:04,433 --> 00:12:05,167
Mother....

121
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:07,967
Mother...

122
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:10,267
Mother, no.

123
00:12:10,333 --> 00:12:12,100
No. Mother, no.

124
00:12:13,767 --> 00:12:14,800
Mother...

125
00:12:16,567 --> 00:12:20,033
Mother, please. Please wake up.

126
00:12:20,100 --> 00:12:21,433
Listen to me.

127
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:23,467
Wake up, Mother.

128
00:14:04,933 --> 00:14:05,433
Mother...

129
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:16,600
Mother...

130
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:23,400
Mother...

131
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:25,600
Mother.

132
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:28,833
Mother.

133
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,933
I'm really trying my best
to forgive.

134
00:14:47,667 --> 00:14:49,700
I'm trying, Mother.

135
00:14:53,500 --> 00:14:56,500
But every time I remember
what father did to you...

136
00:15:02,667 --> 00:15:04,900
When he left you
for someone else.

137
00:15:10,467 --> 00:15:11,967
When he loved someone else...

138
00:15:21,867 --> 00:15:23,500
and you died because of that.

139
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:35,867
You are my only family.

140
00:15:41,233 --> 00:15:41,833
Just you.

141
00:16:01,767 --> 00:16:02,767
I miss you, Mother.

142
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:50,267
I need some fresh air.

143
00:17:11,633 --> 00:17:12,667
My gosh.

144
00:17:15,533 --> 00:17:16,333
Oh my God.

145
00:17:17,467 --> 00:17:21,200
You now belong
to the last season of paradise.

146
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:23,833
That's it for you, Dear.

147
00:18:01,233 --> 00:18:01,967
Much better.

148
00:18:30,333 --> 00:18:35,367
Miss, you may want to buy
some handicrafts from Sorsogon.

149
00:18:35,433 --> 00:18:36,467
Buy one, please.

150
00:18:40,100 --> 00:18:43,900
Celeste!

151
00:18:43,967 --> 00:18:46,633
Celeste, May-May, May-May,
May-May...

152
00:18:47,833 --> 00:18:48,200
May-May.

153
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:51,567
Cousin.

154
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:56,400
I mean, Cuz,
you're sophisticated now.

155
00:18:57,600 --> 00:18:59,200
How are you?

156
00:18:59,267 --> 00:19:00,567
I miss you.

157
00:19:01,567 --> 00:19:04,533
Hey you, just because
you broke up with Mikoy,

158
00:19:04,600 --> 00:19:06,533
you didn't bother
to get in touch with us,

159
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:09,167
your family, and friends.

160
00:19:09,233 --> 00:19:11,367
Why? Do you think
I will judge you?

161
00:19:11,433 --> 00:19:12,300
You're annoying.

162
00:19:13,367 --> 00:19:14,100
I'm sorry.

163
00:19:16,700 --> 00:19:19,733
I was busy in Manila
so we weren't able to talk.

164
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:21,033
Liar of the year.

165
00:19:21,100 --> 00:19:22,000
What busy you're talking about?

166
00:19:23,067 --> 00:19:24,000
You're lying, you vixen.

167
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:34,700
In fairness,
you're more beautiful now.

168
00:19:34,800 --> 00:19:37,267
Cuz, you're really different.

169
00:19:37,333 --> 00:19:40,533
And you smell good too.

170
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:44,467
You are so sophisticated.
You are really beautiful.

171
00:19:44,533 --> 00:19:46,667
Do you know
that I'm your number one fan?

172
00:19:46,733 --> 00:19:48,667
I'm your number one fan.

173
00:19:48,733 --> 00:19:54,100
High heeled world-class
and the diamonds are big, Cuz.

174
00:19:54,167 --> 00:19:56,700
Let's take a selfie,
even just one picture.

175
00:19:56,767 --> 00:19:57,933
I'll tell my friends

176
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:02,300
that I have a famous fashion
designer cousin.

177
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:06,367
A member of the world-class
society, something like that.

178
00:20:06,433 --> 00:20:08,300
What's with you?

179
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:10,733
Heart, like this.

180
00:20:13,300 --> 00:20:14,900
There, you go.

181
00:20:14,967 --> 00:20:17,200
See? We're both beautiful here.

182
00:20:18,700 --> 00:20:21,133
- May, I'm sorry.
- Cuz?

183
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:22,200
When did you arrive?

184
00:20:23,533 --> 00:20:26,367
I arrived this morning.

185
00:20:26,433 --> 00:20:31,967
I'm leaving. I'm going
to the airport until you saw me.

186
00:20:32,033 --> 00:20:34,433
What? Why so fast?

187
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:35,533
What's this?

188
00:20:35,633 --> 00:20:38,200
You just visited Uncle Patricio
in Bulusan

189
00:20:38,267 --> 00:20:40,100
and you will go home right away?

190
00:20:40,167 --> 00:20:41,033
Do you want to go home?

191
00:20:41,967 --> 00:20:42,467
Are you going somewhere else?

192
00:20:43,967 --> 00:20:45,533
Actually, I have a lot of things
to do.

193
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:46,967
I have a lot of appointments
in Manila.

194
00:20:47,033 --> 00:20:49,100
I have to leave.

195
00:20:49,167 --> 00:20:50,700
I'm going to the airport.

196
00:20:50,767 --> 00:20:53,467
Here's what we can do.
You know, send me a DM.

197
00:20:53,533 --> 00:20:56,800
Send me your number
and let's talk.

198
00:20:56,867 --> 00:21:02,067
Or let's catch up, right?

199
00:21:02,133 --> 00:21:04,033
You know, Cuz,
as if you're someone else.

200
00:21:04,100 --> 00:21:06,333
We have to eat chili ice cream
first.

201
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:07,600
Isn't chili your favorite?

202
00:21:08,633 --> 00:21:12,567
When we were kids,
you can eat ten chilies.

203
00:21:12,633 --> 00:21:15,667
Can't you remember that?
You inserted chili in your nose.

204
00:21:15,733 --> 00:21:17,200
That's embarrassing.

205
00:21:17,267 --> 00:21:18,267
Excuse me.

206
00:21:18,333 --> 00:21:19,733
I'm sorry. I just mentioned it.

207
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:21,267
Can I say sorry?

208
00:21:21,333 --> 00:21:22,333
Cuz, come on.

209
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:23,667
Let's talk first.

210
00:21:23,733 --> 00:21:24,800
Hurry, come on.

211
00:21:26,233 --> 00:21:28,300
I'm really sorry.
I have to leave.

212
00:21:28,367 --> 00:21:30,000
So, I really can't.

213
00:21:30,067 --> 00:21:32,000
Come on. Let's grab a bite.

214
00:21:32,067 --> 00:21:33,667
Chili ice cream is delicious.
Come on.

215
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:37,600
Okay, I'll just get my bag
and my shades

216
00:21:37,667 --> 00:21:38,600
because it's a bit hot.

217
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,833
Okay, you come back.

218
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:43,233
- Yes.
- You might go and leave me.

219
00:21:43,333 --> 00:21:43,967
No.

220
00:21:48,267 --> 00:21:50,567
Celeste, did you notice?

221
00:21:50,633 --> 00:21:52,233
A lot of things have changed
here in Sorsogon

222
00:21:52,300 --> 00:21:53,400
since you lived in Manila.

223
00:21:55,333 --> 00:21:58,000
Our town is getting
more beautiful.

224
00:21:59,133 --> 00:22:01,700
You should visit here
more often.

225
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:06,933
And next time you come back,

226
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:09,400
you should bring your boyfriend,
Tonito.

227
00:22:11,700 --> 00:22:14,167
I saw your social media posts.

228
00:22:14,233 --> 00:22:15,967
So, you're getting married.

229
00:22:16,067 --> 00:22:17,367
You know, you're a stalker.

230
00:22:17,433 --> 00:22:21,200
Hey, you're so judgmental.

231
00:22:21,267 --> 00:22:22,300
You're something else.

232
00:22:22,367 --> 00:22:24,267
But he's very handsome.

233
00:22:24,333 --> 00:22:25,533
I think I like him.

234
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:26,433
Does he have a brother?

235
00:22:30,033 --> 00:22:31,800
Just kidding,
you're so gullible.

236
00:22:33,167 --> 00:22:34,700
But this is the first time
I found out

237
00:22:34,767 --> 00:22:36,500
that you like guys
with almond-shaped eyes.

238
00:22:36,567 --> 00:22:37,900
Just like you,
you have almond-shaped eyes.

239
00:22:37,967 --> 00:22:39,467
You look good together,
in fairness.

240
00:22:41,767 --> 00:22:44,700
But his looks are very different
from that of Mikoy's.

241
00:22:44,767 --> 00:22:45,700
Why, Cuz?

242
00:22:50,867 --> 00:22:53,200
How does Mikoy look like now?

243
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:58,667
Well, your ex is still handsome.

244
00:22:58,733 --> 00:22:59,400
He's so yummy!

245
00:23:02,100 --> 00:23:04,233
But a lot has changed
with your ex.

246
00:23:04,300 --> 00:23:05,833
I don't know about him.

247
00:23:08,033 --> 00:23:08,600
What do you mean?

248
00:23:09,767 --> 00:23:12,900
When you broke up, he went home
here in Sorsogon.

249
00:23:13,933 --> 00:23:15,567
He learned to drink.

250
00:23:25,067 --> 00:23:26,033
Who's brave here?

251
00:23:29,500 --> 00:23:30,533
Come out whoever is brave!

252
00:23:47,867 --> 00:23:50,633
Well, we didn't see or talk
to him for several months.

253
00:24:07,167 --> 00:24:09,233
I think Mikoy got depressed
when you broke up.

254
00:24:09,300 --> 00:24:10,033
It was your fault, Cuz.

255
00:24:45,833 --> 00:24:46,700
I feel sorry for him.

256
00:24:50,233 --> 00:24:52,767
Cuz, what did you fight about?

257
00:24:52,833 --> 00:24:54,800
Why did you and Mikoy
suddenly break up?

258
00:24:57,033 --> 00:24:59,833
Actually, I can't remember
anymore.

259
00:24:59,900 --> 00:25:01,667
That was a long time ago.

260
00:25:01,733 --> 00:25:03,067
Do you have amnesia?

261
00:25:03,167 --> 00:25:04,300
What's this?

262
00:25:04,367 --> 00:25:05,900
Did you forget right away?

263
00:25:05,967 --> 00:25:07,967
I know how to get rid
of your amnesia.

264
00:25:08,033 --> 00:25:09,700
Let's just go to Mikoy.

265
00:25:09,767 --> 00:25:10,967
Let's visit him
even just for a moment.

266
00:25:12,633 --> 00:25:16,267
No. I mean, I have to go
to the airport.

267
00:25:16,333 --> 00:25:17,900
- I'm leaving.
- Just for a moment.

268
00:25:17,967 --> 00:25:19,233
Mikoy is just nearby.

269
00:25:19,300 --> 00:25:20,700
Their canteen is nearby.

270
00:25:20,767 --> 00:25:23,033
- It's just there.
- What's with you? It's so hot.

271
00:25:23,100 --> 00:25:24,433
- I can't.
- It's just for a moment.

272
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:26,500
What's with you?

273
00:25:26,567 --> 00:25:28,467
Wait, perfect timing.
Mikoy's here.

274
00:25:28,533 --> 00:25:30,633
There he is. Mikoy!

275
00:25:30,700 --> 00:25:31,300
Mikoy!

276
00:26:48,900 --> 00:26:52,433
You are a very successful
fashion designer now.

277
00:26:52,500 --> 00:26:54,133
I'm glad.

278
00:26:54,200 --> 00:26:55,567
Are you engaged?

279
00:26:55,633 --> 00:26:57,767
Yes, actually.

280
00:26:57,833 --> 00:26:59,000
It's beautiful, right?

281
00:26:59,067 --> 00:27:00,200
When is the wedding?

282
00:27:00,267 --> 00:27:02,300
- Soon.
- Am I invited?

283
00:27:02,367 --> 00:27:03,600
God. It's so awkward.
What's that?

284
00:27:03,667 --> 00:27:05,333
Why does he look at me
like that?

285
00:27:05,400 --> 00:27:06,533
And his smile is like...

286
00:27:08,033 --> 00:27:09,000
what is that?

287
00:27:09,067 --> 00:27:11,567
Is there no spark?

288
00:27:11,633 --> 00:27:12,600
Nothing.

289
00:27:12,667 --> 00:27:16,267
There's no pinch?
The truth, admit it.

290
00:27:16,367 --> 00:27:18,233
Nothing. What's with you?
Celeste is getting married.

291
00:27:20,733 --> 00:27:22,300
I wish we didn't meet.

292
00:27:22,367 --> 00:27:25,367
Reckless imprudence
resulting in damage to property.
